  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Anti-Cancer Drug Regimen - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_anti-cancer_drug_regimen">Anti-Cancer Drug Regimen</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_clinical_intervention">CLINICAL INTERVENTION</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_anti-cancer_drug_regimen">Anti-Cancer Drug Regimen</xref>
 is a prescribed systematic form of treatment for a course of drug(s), comprising one or more 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_anti-cancer_drug_cycle">Anti-Cancer Drug Cycles</xref>
, provided to a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 suffering from cancer.  </p>
  <p>These can include:</p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_chemotherapy">Chemotherapy</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_cytotoxic_chemotherapy">Cytotoxic Chemotherapy</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_hormone_therapy">Hormone Therapy</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_immunotherapy">Immunotherapy</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_systemic_anti-cancer_therapy">Systemic Anti-Cancer Therapy</xref>
            <p>etc</p>
         </div>
      </li>
  </ul>

</body>
